      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(scripts): close local heavy-check lock gaps",
        "body": "## Summary\n- keep the shared local heavy-check lock for type-aware oxlint, including explicit file-target runs that can spawn `tsgolint headless`\n- wrap sharded oxlint in one parent heavy-check lock while child shards skip duplicate locks to avoid self-deadlock\n- stop exempting scoped tooling test runs from the shared heavy-check lock\n- add an opt-in source-checkout install pressure guard so local `pnpm install` can refuse to start when memory/swap/load are already dangerous\n- clean up lint-only failures on the branch, including a stale cron isolated-agent test import\n\n## Why\nA Pi incident showed `tsgolint` entering through type-aware oxlint and consuming ~5.25 GiB RSS while swap was nearly exhausted. Direct `run-tsgo` was guarded, but type-aware oxlint and scoped tooling tests could still bypass the shared lock and run beside other heavy local work.\n\nThe later post-incident sweep found one more practical pressure path: local source-checkout installs could start while the host was already choking. This PR adds an operator-controlled guard for that path without changing default install behavior.\n\n## Behavior\n- Local heavy-check serialization now covers:\n  - type-aware oxlint with explicit file targets\n  - sharded oxlint parent runs\n  - scoped tooling test runs\n- Shard children skip duplicate locking after the parent lock is acquired.\n- Local source-checkout installs refuse under host pressure only when `OPENCLAW_INSTALL_PRESSURE_GUARD=1` is set and any of these are true:\n  - `MemAvailable < 2GiB`\n  - `SwapFree < 1GiB`\n  - `load1 > 10`\n- CI/GitHub Actions skip the install refusal.\n- Without `OPENCLAW_INSTALL_PRESSURE_GUARD=1`, local installs keep the existing warning-only behavior.\n\n## Test Plan\n- `node --check scripts/lib/local-heavy-check-runtime.mjs`\n- `node --check scripts/test-projects.test-support.mjs`\n- `node --check scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs`\n- `node --check scripts/preinstall-package-manager-warning.mjs`\n- `OPENCLAW_TEST_PROJECTS_FORCE_LOCK=1 OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE=throttled pnpm test test/scripts/local-heavy-check-runtime.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts test/scripts/run-oxlint.test.ts test/scripts/preinstall-package-manager-warning.test.ts --run`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 scripts/lib/local-heavy-check-runtime.mjs scripts/test-projects.test-support.mjs scripts/run-oxlint-shards.mjs scripts/preinstall-package-manager-warning.mjs test/scripts/local-heavy-check-runtime.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts test/scripts/run-oxlint.test.ts test/scripts/preinstall-package-manager-warning.test.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint src/agents/tools/cron-tool.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts --threads=1`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/tools/cron-tool.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_LOCAL_CHECK_MODE=throttled pnpm test src/agents/tools/cron-tool.test.ts src/agents/tools/cron-tool.schema.test.ts src/agents/tools/cron-tool.flat-params.test.ts extensions/codex/src/app-server/run-attempt.test.ts --run`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior or issue addressed: The local heavy-check guards now keep type-aware oxlint and sharded oxlint behind the shared local heavy-check lock, avoid duplicate child-shard locking, and add an opt-in install pressure refusal path for source checkouts.\n\nReal environment tested: Real OpenClaw source checkout on Raspberry Pi host, rebased onto current `origin/main` at the time of repair. The host was under real pressure during verification (`SwapFree below 1GiB`, `load1 above 10`), which exercised the opt-in install pressure guard path.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n1. Rebased the PR branch onto current `origin/main`.\n2. Ran `git merge-base --is-ancestor origin/main HEAD`.\n3. Ran `git diff --check origin/main..HEAD`.\n4. Ran `OPENCLAW_INSTALL_PRESSURE_GUARD=1 pnpm test test/scripts/local-heavy-check-runtime.test.ts test/scripts/preinstall-package-manager-warning.test.ts test/scripts/run-oxlint.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts`, which hit the opt-in install pressure guard.\n5. Ran `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/local-heavy-check-runtime.test.ts test/scripts/preinstall-package-manager-warning.test.ts test/scripts/run-oxlint.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts` to verify the targeted behavior without dependency reconciliation in the pressured worktree.\n6. Final caretaker repair at head `762e5dec8eb7621ca8ba4d5820aa15fc73faf94c` removed the stale cron isolated-agent import flagged by CI/review and ran `git diff --check` before pushing. No broad local CI was run on the Raspberry Pi; GitHub Actions is the source of truth for the full matrix.\n\nEvidence after fix: Terminal output from the real Raspberry Pi checkout showed the opt-in `OPENCLAW_INSTALL_PRESSURE_GUARD=1 pnpm test ...` wrapper refusing unsafe local work with `Refusing to run package-manager install/update on this host because SwapFree below 1GiB and load1 above 10`. The same terminal session then showed targeted `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ...` output passing 4 files / 127 tests. The final import cleanup is a direct removal of unused imports from `src/cron/isolated-agent.run-timeout-override.test.ts`, including the missing `../agents/pi-embedded.js` import that failed the cron isolated-agent CI lane.\n\nObserved result after fix: The opt-in runtime guard refused pressured local dependency reconciliation, while the targeted Vitest command passed the affected local-heavy-check behavior without bypassing the guard. The final head no longer imports the missing cron test module, so the previous `ERR_MODULE_NOT_FOUND` blocker is addressed at source.\n\nWhat was not tested: I did not run broad/full local heavy checks on the Raspberry Pi because this change intentionally avoids unsafe heavy local work under pressure. CI remains the broad proof surface for the full matrix.",
        "branch": "fix/local-heavy-check-lock-gaps",
